# 4. 秘密の作戦

Saki: And then, and then, Airi...!
Shiho: Saki... I get you're happy about it, but you've already told this story like ten times.
Saki: What?! Have I been talking about it that much?
Luka: That goes to show how wonderful a memory it is for you.
Saki: Oh! I'm pretty sure I haven't shown you this yet, though!
Saki: You see... I got a picture of me and Airi! Look, look!
Honami: Wow... That's amazing! I'm so glad for you, Saki!
MEIKO: You're looking a little bashful here, Saki.
Saki: I-I mean...! Airi was so dazzling when she was in idol mode...
Saki: My heart really got racing!
Rin: Yeah, I'm sure it would for me too if I got to take a picture like this with somebody I always dreamed of meeting!
Luka: I'm glad you got a precious photo to put in your album.
Miku: So, what other kinds of pictures have you gotten? You've been doing a bunch of the things on your list, right?
Saki: Well... I made a domino chain with Tsukasa... And I studied with my classmates at a diner too!
Saki: Here, these are the pictures!
Honami: Wow... There are dominoes lined up all over the room. Tsukasa looks really serious too.
MEIKO: Your study session also looks like fun. Though, I see you all ordered parfaits, pancakes and other treats.
Len: Way too many... Were you even able to open up your notebooks on that table?
Saki: It's fine, it's fine! Time spent snacking and chatting with friends is all part of the study session experience!
Shiho: (Huh? This picture...)
Saki: Oh, and! This picture is from when me, Ichi and Haruka recorded a challenge video!
Rin: A challenge video?
Honami: That's when people record themselves trying to do something difficult. Like...knocking over a pencil by throwing an eraser from far away.
Ichika: We set out to roll six dice and have them all land on the same number, and it really was an ordeal...
Saki: Yeah! They totally refused to match up, so we rolled like two hundred times!
Shiho: (Yeah, it's the same for this picture...)
Shiho: (Saki's in the photo with Momoi, but most of the other pictures are of other people.)
Shiho: (And even for the ones she is in, she's not fully in frame since she's holding the camera...)
Saki: Huh? I got a message from Mom...
Saki: Ack! I was supposed to pick up the ingredients for dinner today!
Saki: Sorry, everyone! Mom won't be able to make our ginger fried pork if I don't hurry, so I'll head back now!
Honami: Ah, be careful not to trip and fall over!
Saki: Will do! See you all tomorrow! Bye bye!
Ichika: Well, I guess we should start getting ready to head home as well.
Shiho: Um... Hold on a second.
Shiho: There's something I want to talk to you guys about...
Miku: So there aren't many decent pictures of Saki, huh...?
Honami: I was kind of thinking that as well...
Honami: If she's making a photo album, I'm sure it'd be better to have lots of pictures that clearly show her.
Honami: That should make it easier to remember how much fun she had with everyone whenever she looks at it.
Shiho: Yeah... I agree.
Shiho: So, why don't we take pictures of Saki whenever we do the stuff on her list with her?
Honami: Oh...! That way, we can get good pictures of her!
Ichika: Yeah. I think she'll like that...!
Rin: Oh... I've got an idea!
Rin: If you're gonna give her pictures, you should make it a surprise! Don't you think that would make her even happier?!
Shiho: Yeah... Saki tends to enjoy that sort of thing, so that might be good.
Honami: Then we'll have to be as sneaky as possible with our photography.
Ichika: Right. Let's do our best to make sure she loves the surprise!
Saki: Thanks for coming, everybody!
Haruka: I wanted to play with everyone too, so it's my pleasure.
Kohane: It's been a while since I've played, so I'm not sure I'll do well... But I'll try my best!
Emu: You guys! Wh-Wh-Wh-What are we gonna do?!
Honami: What's wrong, Emu?
Emu: So, I went to the gym since I wanted to do some warmup exercises, but there were already some girls there using it!
Saki: Wait, for real?!
Saki: *Sob* I'm sorry! If I'd just run ahead to secure our spot...
Ichika: Don't blame yourself. I hadn't thought about securing a spot either... It's just some bad timing.
Shiho: Then, why don't we go to the schoolyard? If we draw lines in the dirt with our shoes, we can make a court ourselves.
Kohane: Oh... But I heard the softball team is using the schoolyard. They apparently have a practice match coming up.
Saki: Huuuh? What do we do?! And after you all came to join me for this...
Emu: Isn't there any other place that might work...?
???: Hm? What are you all doing gathered around here?
Emu: Oh! Asahina!
Saki: Um... Actually, we're looking for somewhere we can play dodgeball. The gym and the schoolyard are both taken.
Emu: Do you know any good spots, Asahina?
Mafuyu: Dodgeball...? In that case, you'll be able to play as long as there's room to draw up a court, right?
Mafuyu: It might be a bit small, but there's a spot on the way over to the archery range that might work.
Saki: R-Really?!
Mafuyu: Yeah. It's in an area behind the school that people don't go to that often, so I don't think anyone will be using it.
Emu: Wow, thanks so much, Asahina!
Emu: Isn't this great, Saki?☆
Saki: Yeah! Thank you, Emu!
Mafuyu: Well, I'll be off. Have fun, everyone.
Saki: We will!
Emu: Oh...
Emu: W-Wait just a moment, please!
Mafuyu: Otori? What is it?
Emu: Would you like to play dodgeball too, Asahina?
Mafuyu: What...?
Emu: Um... I figure you might be busy with studying and stuff, but...
Emu: I just know this is gonna be suuuper fun!!!
Emu: So, even just for five minutes...!
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: Well...
Mafuyu: Since you insist, maybe I'll take you up on your offer for a bit.
Emu: Wha— R-Really?!
Mafuyu: Sure... I was just thinking that I want to take a breather.
Mafuyu: Thanks for inviting me along, Otori. Is that alright with everyone?
Saki: Yes! Of course!
Mafuyu: Thank you. Then, I'll go get ready.
